                                       Iteration<BindingSet,QueryEvaluationException> rightArg,
                                       AtomicLong used,
                                       long maxSize)
        Creates a new MinusIteration that returns the results of the left argument minus the results of the right argument. By default, duplicates are not filtered from the results.
        Parameters:
        leftArg - An Iteration containing the main set of elements.
        rightArg - An Iteration containing the set of elements that should be filtered from the main set. * @param used An atomic long used to monitor how many elements are in the set collections.
        used - An atomic long used to monitor how many elements are in the set collections.
        maxSize - Maximum size allowed by the sum of all collections used by the LimitedSizeQueryEvaluatlion.

      • LimitedSizeSPARQLMinusIteration

                                       AtomicLong used,
                                       long maxSize)
        Creates a new SPARQLMinusIteration that returns the results of the left argument minus the results of the right argument.
        Parameters:
        leftArg - An Iteration containing the main set of elements.
        rightArg - An Iteration containing the set of elements that should be filtered from the main set.
        distinct - Flag indicating whether duplicate elements should be filtered from the result.
        used - An atomic long used to monitor how many elements are in the set collections.
        maxSize - Maximum size allowed by the sum of all collections used by the LimitedSizeQueryEvaluatlion.
